30/09/2005
LONDON, United Kingdom -- Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski presented Citigroup with investment opportunities in his country on Thursday (29 September). During the presentation, Buckovski noted that Macedonia has achieved political stability and is on the way to economic stability. Economic and political reforms would ensure sustainable development, which would in turn reduce unemployment and improve the business environment, the prime minister said. Citigroup was hired to handle Macedonia's first Eurobond issue. (Government of Macedonia Web site, MIA - 29/09/05)
